===Glyph origin===
Graphical manipulations on {{zh-l|兵|[[soldier]]}}.

===Etymology===
A similar-sounding onomatopoeia to the source character{{zh-l|兵|[[soldier]]}}. First attested in {{w|Ming Dynasty}} and referred to the sound of collisions (during a fight). Later used as a {{translit|zh|en|ping pong|nocap=y}}.

